Sentencas: Composites cathodes consisting of strontium doped lanthanum manganite (LSM) and yttria stabilized zirconia have been impregnated with the nitrates corresponding to the nominal compositions: La(0.75)Sr(0.25)Mn(1.05)O(3 +/-delta) (LSM25), Ce(0.8)Sm(0.2)O(2) (SDC) and a combination of both (dual).
Titulo: Impregnation of LSM Based Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The latter performed best with a polarization resistance (R(P)) of 0.39 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C and 0.039 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C compared to 2.17 and 0.19 Omega cm(2) respectively for electrodes without impregnation.
Titulo: Impregnation of LSM Based Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Furthermore the dual impregnation decreased the activation energy of R(P) to 1.19 eV compared to 1.35 eV for cells without impregnation.
Titulo: Impregnation of LSM Based Cathodes for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
